column1: In the 90 years since Rebecca Felton of Georgia became the first woman in the United States Senate - sworn in for a mere 24 hours - women remain an anomaly in the upper chamber. But with 20 female senators now in office , an all-time high , women have morphed from the curiosity they were for much of the 20th century into an important new force on key committees and legislation.
